instruction: Given two data sets, compare the two and explain how they differ.
output: Data Set 1 and Data Set 2 have similarities in the Y column, as their values are all 3s. However, the values in the X column are different. In Data Set 1, the values in X are [1,2,3], while in Data Set 2, the values in X are [3,3,1].
